    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error Correction Loops"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Error detection tells you what went wrong; error correction loops close the cycle by acting on that signal. A correction loop wraps a step execution: run it, detect errors, attempt a fix, run again \u2014 until the output is clean or a retry budget is exhausted."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Error Correction Loop flow",
          "title": "Execute \u2192 Detect \u2192 Correct \u2192 Accept or Abort"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Key principle:"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " correction loops must be bounded. An unbounded loop that never converges consumes tokens indefinitely. Always set a "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "max_retries"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " ceiling and detect non-convergence early."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Basic Correction Loop"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The simplest correction loop is a class that pairs a detection function with a correction function. The detection function returns a list of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "DetectedError"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " objects; the correction function takes the errored output and those errors and returns a revised output."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\nfrom typing import Callable, Any\n\n@dataclass\nclass CorrectionLoop:\n    \"\"\"Wraps a step execution with detect-and-correct retries.\"\"\"\n    detect_fn: Callable[[Any], list[DetectedError]]\n    correct_fn: Callable[[Any, list[DetectedError]], Any]\n    max_retries: int = 3\n\n    def run(self, execute_fn: Callable[[], Any]) -> Any:\n        result = execute_fn()\n        for attempt in range(self.max_retries):\n            errors = self.detect_fn(result)\n            if not errors:\n                return result\n            result = self.correct_fn(result, errors)\n        # Final check after last correction\n        if self.detect_fn(result):\n            raise RuntimeError('Correction loop exhausted without resolving errors')\n        return result\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The loop attempts correction up to "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "max_retries"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " times. A final check after the last correction ensures we do not silently return a still-broken result."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "LLM-Based Correction"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For semantic or structural errors that a deterministic function cannot fix, pass the error list back to the model as a corrective prompt. The model sees its original output, the list of reported errors, and the original objective \u2014 and rewrites the output."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\ndef llm_correct(\n    original_output: str,\n    errors: list[DetectedError],\n    objective: str,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Ask the model to rewrite the output, fixing each reported error.\"\"\"\n    error_list = '\\n'.join(\n        f'- [{e.layer}] {e.error_type}: {e.message}' for e in errors\n    )\n    prompt = (\n        f'Your previous output had errors:\\n{error_list}\\n\\n'\n        f'Original output:\\n{original_output}\\n\\n'\n        f'Objective: {objective}\\n\\n'\n        'Fix every listed error and return the corrected output ONLY. '\n        'Do not explain your changes.'\n    )\n    response = client.messages.create(\n        model='claude-sonnet-4-6',\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        messages=[{'role': 'user', 'content': prompt}],\n    )\n    return response.content[0].text\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Prompt discipline:"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " instruct the model to return the corrected output only, with no preamble. A model that says \"Sure, here is the corrected version:\" before the output forces you to strip that prefix before re-validating."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Stateful Loop Tracking"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "LoopState"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " dataclass records every output and its error list across attempts. This creates an audit trail for debugging and enables convergence detection: if two consecutive attempts produce the same error set, the loop is stuck and should abort."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\n@dataclass\nclass LoopState:\n    step_id: str\n    attempt: int = 0\n    outputs: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    error_history: list[list[DetectedError]] = field(default_factory=list)\n    resolved: bool = False\n\n    @property\n    def current_output(self) -> str | None:\n        return self.outputs[-1] if self.outputs else None\n\n    def record(self, output: str, errors: list[DetectedError]) -> None:\n        self.outputs.append(output)\n        self.error_history.append(errors)\n        self.attempt += 1\n        if not errors:\n            self.resolved = True\n\ndef run_stateful_correction(\n    client,\n    step_id: str,\n    execute_fn: Callable[[], str],\n    detect_fn: Callable[[str], list[DetectedError]],\n    objective: str,\n    max_retries: int = 3,\n) -> LoopState:\n    state = LoopState(step_id=step_id)\n    result = execute_fn()\n    errors = detect_fn(result)\n    state.record(result, errors)\n    while not state.resolved and state.attempt < max_retries:\n        corrected = llm_correct(state.current_output, state.error_history[-1], objective)\n        errors = detect_fn(corrected)\n        state.record(corrected, errors)\n    return state  # caller checks state.resolved\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The caller checks "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "state.resolved"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to know whether correction succeeded, and can inspect "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "state.error_history"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to understand what went wrong across attempts."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Crafting Effective Correction Prompts"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The quality of the corrected output depends heavily on how the error list is formatted in the prompt. Enumerate errors by index so the model can address each one explicitly. Include both the objective and the success criteria so the model has enough context to correct without introducing new problems."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "CORRECTION_SYSTEM = (\n    'You are a precise output corrector. You receive an output, a list of '\n    'errors, and the original objective. Return ONLY the corrected output '\n    'with every listed error addressed. Do not add commentary or apologies.'\n)\n\ndef build_correction_prompt(\n    output: str,\n    errors: list[DetectedError],\n    objective: str,\n    success_criteria: list[str],\n) -> str:\n    criteria_text = '\\n'.join(f'- {c}' for c in success_criteria)\n    error_text = '\\n'.join(\n        f'{i+1}. [{e.layer}/{e.error_type}] {e.message}'\n        for i, e in enumerate(errors)\n    )\n    return (\n        f'OBJECTIVE: {objective}\\n'\n        f'SUCCESS CRITERIA:\\n{criteria_text}\\n\\n'\n        f'ERRORS TO FIX:\\n{error_text}\\n\\n'\n        f'CURRENT OUTPUT:\\n{output}\\n\\n'\n        'Return the corrected output directly.'\n    )\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Use a dedicated system prompt: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "separating the corrector's role (\"fix errors\") from the original actor's role prevents the model from confusing its two tasks."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Number each error: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "numbered lists help the model systematically address each issue rather than only fixing the most prominent one."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ],
                    "text": "Quote the original output verbatim: "
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "if the model cannot see exactly what it produced, it may correct a phantom output rather than the actual one."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Convergence Detection"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When errors persist across consecutive correction attempts, continued retrying wastes tokens without making progress. Compare the current error set to the previous one \u2014 if they are identical, the model cannot resolve the issue with the current prompt and should abort."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def has_converged(\n    prev_errors: list[DetectedError],\n    curr_errors: list[DetectedError],\n) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"True when correction is making no progress.\"\"\"\n    prev_keys = {(e.layer, e.error_type, e.message) for e in prev_errors}\n    curr_keys = {(e.layer, e.error_type, e.message) for e in curr_errors}\n    return prev_keys == curr_keys\n\ndef run_adaptive_correction(\n    client,\n    execute_fn: Callable[[], str],\n    detect_fn: Callable[[str], list[DetectedError]],\n    objective: str,\n    criteria: list[str],\n    max_retries: int = 3,\n) -> tuple[str, bool]:\n    \"\"\"Returns (final_output, success). Stops early on non-convergence.\"\"\"\n    output = execute_fn()\n    prev_errors: list[DetectedError] = []\n    for _ in range(max_retries):\n        errors = detect_fn(output)\n        if not errors:\n            return output, True\n        if prev_errors and has_converged(prev_errors, errors):\n            break  # stuck \u2014 further retries won't help\n        prompt = build_correction_prompt(output, errors, objective, criteria)\n        response = client.messages.create(\n            model='claude-sonnet-4-6',\n            max_tokens=1024,\n            system=CORRECTION_SYSTEM,\n            messages=[{'role': 'user', 'content': prompt}],\n        )\n        output = response.content[0].text\n        prev_errors = errors\n    return output, False\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "has_converged"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " function uses a frozenset key of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "(layer, error_type, message)"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " tuples. A partial improvement (fewer errors) is not convergence \u2014 only exact repetition is."
          }
        ]
      },
