      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Testing Correction Loops"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Unit tests for correction loops should cover three scenarios: success on the first attempt (no correction needed), success after one correction, and exhaustion (correction never resolves the error). Use deterministic mock functions for detection and correction to keep tests fast and repeatable."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import pytest\nfrom unittest.mock import MagicMock\n\ndef test_correction_loop_succeeds_on_second_attempt():\n    call_count = 0\n\n    def execute_fn():\n        nonlocal call_count\n        call_count += 1\n        return 'bad output' if call_count == 1 else 'good output'\n\n    def detect_fn(output):\n        return [DetectedError('rule', 'too_short', 'output too short', True)]\n        if output == 'bad output' else []\n\n    def correct_fn(output, errors):\n        return 'good output'  # deterministic fix for testing\n\n    loop = CorrectionLoop(detect_fn=detect_fn, correct_fn=correct_fn)\n    result = loop.run(execute_fn)\n    assert result == 'good output'\n    assert call_count == 1  # execute_fn called once; correct_fn did the fix\n\ndef test_correction_loop_raises_when_exhausted():\n    def always_bad():\n        return 'broken'\n\n    def always_errors(output):\n        return [DetectedError('schema', 'parse_failure', 'cannot parse', True)]\n\n    def noop_correct(output, errors):\n        return output  # correction does nothing\n\n    loop = CorrectionLoop(detect_fn=always_errors, correct_fn=noop_correct, max_retries=2)\n    with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match='exhausted'):\n        loop.run(always_bad)\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Test the "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ],
            "text": "noop_correct"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " scenario explicitly \u2014 it guards against a bug where the loop accepts a still-broken result after exhausting retries."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "End-to-End Integration"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "In a real agent pipeline, the correction loop wraps a single step call. The integration point is: execute the step prompt, pipe the output through the layered error detection pipeline from Error Detection, then apply LLM correction if errors are found. The loop is transparent to the orchestrator \u2014 it returns a clean output or raises."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Full integration: detection + LLM correction + loop\n\nfrom anthropic import Anthropic\n\nclient = Anthropic()\n\ndef run_step_with_correction(\n    step_prompt: str,\n    objective: str,\n    criteria: list[str],\n    max_retries: int = 3,\n) -> tuple[str, bool]:\n    \"\"\"Execute a prompt, detect errors, LLM-correct, and return (output, success).\"\"\"\n    def execute():\n        r = client.messages.create(\n            model='claude-sonnet-4-6',\n            max_tokens=1024,\n            messages=[{'role': 'user', 'content': step_prompt}],\n        )\n        return r.content[0].text\n\n    def detect(output: str) -> list[DetectedError]:\n        # Use the layered detect_errors pipeline from Error Detection\n        return detect_errors(\n            client=client,\n            output=output,\n            raw_output=output,\n            objective=objective,\n            criteria=criteria,\n        )\n\n    output, success = run_adaptive_correction(\n        client=client,\n        execute_fn=execute,\n        detect_fn=detect,\n        objective=objective,\n        criteria=criteria,\n        max_retries=max_retries,\n    )\n    return output, success\n\n# Usage:\nresult, ok = run_step_with_correction(\n    step_prompt='Summarize the meeting notes in exactly 3 bullet points.',\n    objective='Produce a 3-bullet meeting summary',\n    criteria=['exactly 3 bullets', 'each bullet under 20 words'],\n)\nif not ok:\n    print('Step could not be corrected after retries')\n"
          }
        ]
